One Student At PCEA Bahati Girls Has Been Confirmed Dead Due To Heavy Smoke From An Inferno That Razed Down Part Of A Dormitory In The School. 71 Other Students Who Were Affected Were Rushed To Hospital 68 Of Whom Were Discharged While Two Are Still Admitted At Mediheal Hospital In Nakuru. The Chairman Of The Board Of Management At The School Francis Mbugua Says Learning Will Go On As They Repair The Dormitory.